{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019v6XqiGVwSMkSL7Z8qKDyM","type":"tool_result","content":"Available sheets: ['Vendor Analysis Assessment', 'Top 3 Opportunities', 'Methodology', 'CEOCFO Recommendations', 'Config']\r\n\r\n=== TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES SHEET ===\r\n\r\nRow 1: (None, 'Opportunity', 'Explanation', 'Estimated Annual Savings (USD)')\r\nRow 2: ('Opportunity 1', 'Renegotiate Salesforce Enterprise Contract', '� Salesforce at $3.1M is 40% of total portfolio spend.\\n� Audit active seats; renegotiate multi-year terms; bundle Slack billing.\\n� 10�15% savings target reduces single-vendor concentration risk.', 389653)\r\nRow 3: ('Opportunity 2', 'Exit Long-tail Vendor Portfolio', '� 344 vendors under $50K total $1.55M with minimal strategic value.\\n� Issue termination notices; redirect spend to preferred panel vendors.\\n� 10�20% realised after notice periods and minimum commitments.', 232893)\r\nRow 4: ('Opportunity 3', 'Consolidate Global Office Footprint', '� Eight flexible office vendors total $956K with significant overlap.\\n� Exit GPT, WeWork, Work Easy; retain TOG, Innovent, Zagrebtower.\\n� 15�20% cost reduction through lease exits and anchor renegotiations.', 167239)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DHNY6e1BJzp7emMNMCnz41","session_id":"287e74d1-c222-46fc-97c3-6b14ad8ff5d8","uuid":"6147655f-3987-4850-af38-221bb01ddab3","timestamp":"2026-03-20T21:41:10.160Z"}
