{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DHNY6e1BJzp7emMNMCnz41","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information you requested. Here's the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n### 1. **project_vendor_spend_analysis.md**\nThis file contains STEP 03 vendor spend analysis results:\n- **Total vendors:** 386, **Total spend:** $7,887,360.40\n- **Largest vendor:** Salesforce UK ($3,117,225.89 — 39.5% of total)\n- **Spend Tiers:**\n  - High Spend (>$200K): 5 vendors = $4,290,787 (54.4%)\n  - Medium Spend ($50K–$200K): 21 vendors = $1,956,559 (24.8%)\n  - Low Spend (<$50K): 360 vendors = $1,640,014 (20.8%)\n- **Top 10 vendors = 63.9% of spend; Top 5 = 54.3%**\n- Key opportunities: Salesforce concentration risk, 344 Terminate vendors = $1.55M savings, 17 Consolidate vendors = $145K\n\n### 2. **project_step06_rationale.md**\nThis file documents decision rationale for all 385 vendors:\n- **27 OPTIMIZE vendors** including Salesforce ($3.1M), Navan ($357.9K), BDO ($343K), TOG ($263.8K), Cloudcrossing ($208.7K), and others\n- **22 CONSOLIDATE vendors** (duplicate entities and overlapping platforms)\n- **285 TERMINATE vendors** organized by pattern (incidental facilities, redundant SaaS, one-off legal/professional, fragmented finance/accounting, regional engineering, sales & marketing tools, M&A advisory)\n- **Top 3 Cost Optimisation Opportunities:**\n  1. Salesforce renegotiation: $3.1M with 10–20% target = $311K–$623K savings\n  2. Navan consolidation: $415.9K combined with 15–20% target = $62K–$83K savings\n  3. BDO + RSM finance advisory: $460.1K combined with 15–25% target = $69K–$115K savings\n\n### 3. **project_step07_consolidation.md**\nThis file identifies 21 consolidation opportunity groups across 4 priority tiers:\n- **Priority 1 (≥$200K):** 6 groups, ~$5.35M\n  - CRM/Marketing ($3.15M): Salesforce + HubSpot\n  - Flexible office ($955K): 8 vendors consolidated to 3 anchors\n  - Accounting/Audit ($533K): Multiple firms consolidated to BDO + RSM\n  - Travel management ($415K): Navan entities merged\n  - Cloud services ($390K): AWS, Cloudcrossing, Cloud Tech Solutions merged\n  - Health insurance ($197K): Multiple insurers consolidated\n- **Priority 2 ($50K–$200K):** 5 groups, ~$866K (Telecom, M&A Advisory, Marketing Agency, HR Services, Sales Intelligence)\n- **Priority 3 ($10K–$50K):** 6 groups, ~$241K (recruiting, accounting SaaS, industry association, employee engagement, benefits, integration platform)\n- **Priority 4 (<$10K):** 4 groups, ~$26K (corporate secretarial, hardware, Atlassian-Trello, logistics)\n- **Total in scope:** ~$6.48M (82.2% of portfolio)\n\n### 4. **project_step08_strategic_scores.md**\nThis file provides strategic importance scores (1–5) for all 386 vendors with conflict analysis:\n- **Score 5 (Mission critical):** Salesforce UK, AWS LLC\n- **Score 4 (Strategic):** Google Ireland, Microsoft Ireland\n- **Score 3 (Important but substitutable):** 10+ vendors including BDO, Navan, Cloudcrossing, Infosys, LinkedIn, Kimble\n- **Score 2 (Marginal value):** 40+ vendors including TOG, Innovent, Jensten, Aetna, and many consolidation targets\n- **Score 1 (Redundant/low-value):** 295+ vendors correctly flagged for termination\n- **79 conflicts identified (20% of portfolio):**\n  - 23 Optimize→Consolidate (scoring 2–3, suggesting reclassification needed)\n  - 14 Consolidate conflicts (duplicate AP entities = soft conflicts)\n  - 42 Terminate→Consolidate (genuine omissions with ongoing platform value like Sage, Planful, Workato, Peakon)\n\n---\n\n## \"Top 3 Opportunities\" Sheet Data\n\n| Row | Opportunity | Explanation | Estimated Annual Savings |\n|-----|-------------|-------------|--------------------------|\n| **1** | **Renegotiate Salesforce Enterprise Contract** | Salesforce at $3.1M is 40% of total portfolio spend. Audit active seats; renegotiate multi-year terms; bundle Slack billing. 10–15% savings target reduces single-vendor concentration risk. | **$389,653** |\n| **2** | **Exit Long-tail Vendor Portfolio** | 344 vendors under $50K total $1.55M with minimal strategic value. Issue termination notices; redirect spend to preferred panel vendors. 10–20% realised after notice periods and minimum commitments. | **$232,893** |\n| **3** | **Consolidate Global Office Footprint** | Eight flexible office vendors total $956K with significant overlap. Exit GPT, WeWork, Work Easy; retain TOG, Innovent, Zagrebtower. 15–20% cost reduction through lease exits and anchor renegotiations. | **$167,239** |\n\n**Total Estimated Savings from Top 3 Opportunities: $789,785**"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6d9a14f80b7d9d2e (use SendMessage with to: 'a6d9a14f80b7d9d2e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34901\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 96180</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"287e74d1-c222-46fc-97c3-6b14ad8ff5d8","uuid":"81cfa7a6-5233-464a-a513-b019a984f59f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T21:41:28.851Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following memory files and return their full contents:\n1. C:/Users/rjega/.claude/projects/C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis/memory/project_vendor_spend_analysis.md\n2. C:/Users/rjega/.claude/projects/C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis/memory/project_step06_rationale.md\n3. C:/Users/rjega/.claude/projects/C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis/memory/project_step07_consolidation.md\n4. C:/Users/rjega/.claude/projects/C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis/memory/project_step08_strategic_scores.md\n\nThen, run this Python script to extract the \"Top 3 Opportunities\" sheet from the workbook:\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\")\nprint(\"Sheets:\", wb.sheetnames)\nws = wb[\"Top 3 Opportunities\"]\nfor row in ws.iter_rows(values_only=True):\n    print(row)\n```\n\nReturn all file contents and the script output.","agentId":"a6d9a14f80b7d9d2e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information you requested. Here's the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n### 1. **project_vendor_spend_analysis.md**\nThis file contains STEP 03 vendor spend analysis results:\n- **Total vendors:** 386, **Total spend:** $7,887,360.40\n- **Largest vendor:** Salesforce UK ($3,117,225.89 — 39.5% of total)\n- **Spend Tiers:**\n  - High Spend (>$200K): 5 vendors = $4,290,787 (54.4%)\n  - Medium Spend ($50K–$200K): 21 vendors = $1,956,559 (24.8%)\n  - Low Spend (<$50K): 360 vendors = $1,640,014 (20.8%)\n- **Top 10 vendors = 63.9% of spend; Top 5 = 54.3%**\n- Key opportunities: Salesforce concentration risk, 344 Terminate vendors = $1.55M savings, 17 Consolidate vendors = $145K\n\n### 2. **project_step06_rationale.md**\nThis file documents decision rationale for all 385 vendors:\n- **27 OPTIMIZE vendors** including Salesforce ($3.1M), Navan ($357.9K), BDO ($343K), TOG ($263.8K), Cloudcrossing ($208.7K), and others\n- **22 CONSOLIDATE vendors** (duplicate entities and overlapping platforms)\n- **285 TERMINATE vendors** organized by pattern (incidental facilities, redundant SaaS, one-off legal/professional, fragmented finance/accounting, regional engineering, sales & marketing tools, M&A advisory)\n- **Top 3 Cost Optimisation Opportunities:**\n  1. Salesforce renegotiation: $3.1M with 10–20% target = $311K–$623K savings\n  2. Navan consolidation: $415.9K combined with 15–20% target = $62K–$83K savings\n  3. BDO + RSM finance advisory: $460.1K combined with 15–25% target = $69K–$115K savings\n\n### 3. **project_step07_consolidation.md**\nThis file identifies 21 consolidation opportunity groups across 4 priority tiers:\n- **Priority 1 (≥$200K):** 6 groups, ~$5.35M\n  - CRM/Marketing ($3.15M): Salesforce + HubSpot\n  - Flexible office ($955K): 8 vendors consolidated to 3 anchors\n  - Accounting/Audit ($533K): Multiple firms consolidated to BDO + RSM\n  - Travel management ($415K): Navan entities merged\n  - Cloud services ($390K): AWS, Cloudcrossing, Cloud Tech Solutions merged\n  - Health insurance ($197K): Multiple insurers consolidated\n- **Priority 2 ($50K–$200K):** 5 groups, ~$866K (Telecom, M&A Advisory, Marketing Agency, HR Services, Sales Intelligence)\n- **Priority 3 ($10K–$50K):** 6 groups, ~$241K (recruiting, accounting SaaS, industry association, employee engagement, benefits, integration platform)\n- **Priority 4 (<$10K):** 4 groups, ~$26K (corporate secretarial, hardware, Atlassian-Trello, logistics)\n- **Total in scope:** ~$6.48M (82.2% of portfolio)\n\n### 4. **project_step08_strategic_scores.md**\nThis file provides strategic importance scores (1–5) for all 386 vendors with conflict analysis:\n- **Score 5 (Mission critical):** Salesforce UK, AWS LLC\n- **Score 4 (Strategic):** Google Ireland, Microsoft Ireland\n- **Score 3 (Important but substitutable):** 10+ vendors including BDO, Navan, Cloudcrossing, Infosys, LinkedIn, Kimble\n- **Score 2 (Marginal value):** 40+ vendors including TOG, Innovent, Jensten, Aetna, and many consolidation targets\n- **Score 1 (Redundant/low-value):** 295+ vendors correctly flagged for termination\n- **79 conflicts identified (20% of portfolio):**\n  - 23 Optimize→Consolidate (scoring 2–3, suggesting reclassification needed)\n  - 14 Consolidate conflicts (duplicate AP entities = soft conflicts)\n  - 42 Terminate→Consolidate (genuine omissions with ongoing platform value like Sage, Planful, Workato, Peakon)\n\n---\n\n## \"Top 3 Opportunities\" Sheet Data\n\n| Row | Opportunity | Explanation | Estimated Annual Savings |\n|-----|-------------|-------------|--------------------------|\n| **1** | **Renegotiate Salesforce Enterprise Contract** | Salesforce at $3.1M is 40% of total portfolio spend. Audit active seats; renegotiate multi-year terms; bundle Slack billing. 10–15% savings target reduces single-vendor concentration risk. | **$389,653** |\n| **2** | **Exit Long-tail Vendor Portfolio** | 344 vendors under $50K total $1.55M with minimal strategic value. Issue termination notices; redirect spend to preferred panel vendors. 10–20% realised after notice periods and minimum commitments. | **$232,893** |\n| **3** | **Consolidate Global Office Footprint** | Eight flexible office vendors total $956K with significant overlap. Exit GPT, WeWork, Work Easy; retain TOG, Innovent, Zagrebtower. 15–20% cost reduction through lease exits and anchor renegotiations. | **$167,239** |\n\n**Total Estimated Savings from Top 3 Opportunities: $789,785**"}],"totalDurationMs":96180,"totalTokens":34901,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":684,"cache_read_input_tokens":32793,"output_tokens":1422,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":684},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LgxkHXtefWwrKHdpJBxao3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me analyze the data and perform the quality review.\n\n**STEP 14: Quality Review**\n\nLet me go through each review area:\n\n## 1. DEPARTMENT ACCURACY\n\nI need to check against the common corrections list. Let me think through the vendors mentioned in the memories:\n\nFrom the Step 06 rationale, the key vendors are:\n- Salesforce - CRM → should be Sales/Marketing\n- Navan - Travel management\n- BDO, RSM - Finance/Accounting advisory\n- TOG, Innovent, Zagrebtower - Flexible Office\n- AWS - Cloud/Engineering\n\n\n- Cloudcrossing - Cloud/Engineering\n- Google Ireland, Microsoft Ireland - Engineering/SaaS\n- LinkedIn - mentioned in Step 08 as Score 3\n\nNow I'm cross-referencing the department corrections for tools like Stripe, NetSuite, and QuickBooks which belong in Finance; Workday, BambooHR, and Gusto in G&A; support platforms like Intercom and Zendesk; LinkedIn which could be G&A for recruiting or Marketing for ads; security tools like Okta, CrowdStrike, and Snyk in Engineering; and advisory firms like Deloitte, KPMG, PwC, and EY that should be categorized as M&A if they're providing transaction advisory services.\n\nI realize I don't have direct visibility into the actual department assignments in the workbook itself, and the instructions say I shouldn't re-read the full Vendor Analysis sheet since all the classifications should already be in context from the earlier steps. Looking back at what's captured in the Step 08 memory, I can see some vendor categorizations but the actual department assignments aren't fully documented there. From Step 06, I can see references to terminating redundant SaaS and fragmented finance/accounting vendors, which suggests some miscategorizations occurred. The clearest reference I have is Salesforce UK being marked as CRM/Sales.\n\nThe real issue is that without explicitly reviewing the workbook, I can't definitively say whether vendors like Stripe, NetSuite, QuickBooks, Workday, BambooHR, Gusto, Intercom, Zendesk, Okta, CrowdStrike, Snyk, LinkedIn, Carta, or Pulley were assigned to the wrong departments. The memory doesn't track those specific department assignments, so I need to work with what's actually documented in the earlier steps rather than making assumptions. Looking at the CRM consolidation group, Salesforce is marked as OPTIMIZE while HubSpot appears in the same $3.15M bucket, which suggests HubSpot should be CONSOLIDATE instead. For infrastructure, AWS scores as mission-critical so it should definitely stay OPTIMIZE, and the same logic applies to Azure and GCP—these core platforms should never be terminated.\n\nI'm also noticing some classification conflicts from Step 08: there are 42 vendors flagged as Terminate→Consolidate (like Sage, Planful, Workato, Peakon) that actually have ongoing platform value and might need reclassification, plus 23 more in the Optimize→Consolidate range that are scoring lower and could shift categories.\n\nNow I'm moving into the top opportunities section.  The current ranking shows Salesforce renegotiation at $389K, exiting the long-tail at $232K, and consolidating the office footprint at $167K, but these don't align with the earlier Step 06 estimates where Salesforce was projected at $311K–$623K with a midpoint around $467K. Step 07's deeper consolidation analysis uncovered larger potential in accounting/audit services ($80K–$133K from a $533K spend) and travel management, which suggests the current Top 3 might be underestimating some opportunities. K × 17.5% = $167K vs $533K × say 20% = $106K. So the office one actually generates more savings.\n\nWhat about the Navan travel consolidation? $415K × 17.5% = $73K - smaller.\n\nActually the current Top 3 look well-selected and the savings figures are mathematically sound.\n\nSo I need to do a proper quality review by checking the workbook. The instructions say I shouldn't re-read the full Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet, but I should verify the Top 3 Opportunities sheet and spot-check specific vendors. I can flag common issues and check a subset for department accuracy, though I can't fully verify without reading the Vendor Analysis sheet.\n\nFor recommendation accuracy, I'm recalling from memory that Salesforce and HubSpot should have one marked as CONSOLIDATE, and there were reclassifications needed from the conflict resolution steps - 42 Terminate→Consolidate and 23 Optimize→Consolidate. The Top 3 Opportunities already check out. But to actually make corrections to the workbook, I need to know the exact cell locations, and I'm realizing I need to be more careful about what information I actually have in context versus what I'm working from memory.\n\nLooking at the 79 conflicts flagged in Step 08, I'm not sure if those were resolved or if Step 14 is supposed to address them now.\n\nGiven the constraints about preserving the sheet structure and only updating specific cells, I think the best approach is to write a script that checks the specific vendors I can identify from the department accuracy list and verifies their recommendations are correct, then make targeted corrections where needed.\n\nWriting vendor verification script...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1974,"cache_read_input_tokens":16334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1974,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"287e74d1-c222-46fc-97c3-6b14ad8ff5d8","uuid":"53c894ac-2f2b-4888-892d-774299c91394"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LgxkHXtefWwrKHdpJBxao3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017whx8DbFMNrVBET8tyYpbD","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Spot-check specific vendors in workbook","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"Run the following Python script to spot-check specific vendors in the workbook. Return the COMPLETE output exactly.\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\")\n\n# Identify the Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet\nprint(\"Sheets:\", wb.sheetnames)\n\n# Find the sheet with vendor data\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if \"vendor\" in name.lower() or \"analysis\" in name.lower() or \"assessment\" in name.lower():\n        ws = wb[name]\n        print(f\"Using sheet: {name}\")\n        break\n\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\n    print(f\"Using active sheet: {ws.title}\")\n\n# Read header row to find column positions\nheaders = {}\nfor col in range(1, ws.max_column + 1):\n    val = ws.cell(1, col).value\n    if val:\n        headers[str(val).strip().lower()] = col\n        print(f\"Col {col}: {val}\")\n\n# Vendors to spot-check\ntarget_vendors = [\n    \"stripe\", \"netsuite\", \"quickbooks\", \"workday\", \"bamboohr\", \"gusto\",\n    \"intercom\", \"zendesk\", \"linkedin\", \"okta\", \"crowdstrike\", \"snyk\",\n    \"deloitte\", \"kpmg\", \"pwc\", \"pricewaterhousecoopers\", \"ey \", \"ernst\",\n    \"carta\", \"pulley\", \"hubspot\", \"sage\", \"planful\", \"workato\", \"peakon\",\n    \"upwork\", \"toptal\", \"xero\"\n]\n\nprint(\"\\n=== TARGETED VENDOR SEARCH ===\")\nresults = []\nfor row in range(2, ws.max_row + 1):\n    vendor_cell = ws.cell(row, 1).value  # Assume vendor name in col 1\n    if vendor_cell:\n        vendor_lower = str(vendor_cell).lower()\n        for t in target_vendors:\n            if t in vendor_lower:\n                # Get all values for this row\n                row_vals = [ws.cell(row, c).value for c in range(1, min(ws.max_column+1, 15))]\n                results.append((row, row_vals))\n                print(f\"Row {row}: {row_vals}\")\n                break\n\nprint(f\"\\nTotal matches: {len(results)}\")\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1974,"cache_read_input_tokens":16334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1974,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":13,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"287e74d1-c222-46fc-97c3-6b14ad8ff5d8","uuid":"e7fbd8a0-40c9-4af8-88f1-82437beef891"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a7d9822c30253f2f3","tool_use_id":"toolu_017whx8DbFMNrVBET8tyYpbD","description":"Spot-check specific vendors in workbook","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Run the following Python script to spot-check specific vendors in the workbook. Return the COMPLETE output exactly.\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\")\n\n# Identify the Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet\nprint(\"Sheets:\", wb.sheetnames)\n\n# Find the sheet with vendor data\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if \"vendor\" in name.lower() or \"analysis\" in name.lower() or \"assessment\" in name.lower():\n        ws = wb[name]\n        print(f\"Using sheet: {name}\")\n        break\n\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\n    print(f\"Using active sheet: {ws.title}\")\n\n# Read header row to find column positions\nheaders = {}\nfor col in range(1, ws.max_column + 1):\n    val = ws.cell(1, col).value\n    if val:\n        headers[str(val).strip().lower()] = col\n        print(f\"Col {col}: {val}\")\n\n# Vendors to spot-check\ntarget_vendors = [\n    \"stripe\", \"netsuite\", \"quickbooks\", \"workday\", \"bamboohr\", \"gusto\",\n    \"intercom\", \"zendesk\", \"linkedin\", \"okta\", \"crowdstrike\", \"snyk\",\n    \"deloitte\", \"kpmg\", \"pwc\", \"pricewaterhousecoopers\", \"ey \", \"ernst\",\n    \"carta\", \"pulley\", \"hubspot\", \"sage\", \"planful\", \"workato\", \"peakon\",\n    \"upwork\", \"toptal\", \"xero\"\n]\n\nprint(\"\\n=== TARGETED VENDOR SEARCH ===\")\nresults = []\nfor row in range(2, ws.max_row + 1):\n    vendor_cell = ws.cell(row, 1).value  # Assume vendor name in col 1\n    if vendor_cell:\n        vendor_lower = str(vendor_cell).lower()\n        for t in target_vendors:\n            if t in vendor_lower:\n                # Get all values for this row\n                row_vals = [ws.cell(row, c).value for c in range(1, min(ws.max_column+1, 15))]\n                results.append((row, row_vals))\n                print(f\"Row {row}: {row_vals}\")\n                break\n\nprint(f\"\\nTotal matches: {len(results)}\")\n```\n","uuid":"7cf20261-de63-4d5b-b515-567e0f59c845","session_id":"287e74d1-c222-46fc-97c3-6b14ad8ff5d8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the following Python script to spot-check specific vendors in the workbook. Return the COMPLETE output exactly.\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\")\n\n# Identify the Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet\nprint(\"Sheets:\", wb.sheetnames)\n\n# Find the sheet with vendor data\nws = None\nfor name in wb.sheetnames:\n    if \"vendor\" in name.lower() or \"analysis\" in name.lower() or \"assessment\" in name.lower():\n        ws = wb[name]\n        print(f\"Using sheet: {name}\")\n        break\n\nif ws is None:\n    ws = wb.active\n    print(f\"Using active sheet: {ws.title}\")\n\n# Read header row to find column positions\nheaders = {}\nfor col in range(1, ws.max_column + 1):\n    val = ws.cell(1, col).value\n    if val:\n        headers[str(val).strip().lower()] = col\n        print(f\"Col {col}: {val}\")\n\n# Vendors to spot-check\ntarget_vendors = [\n    \"stripe\", \"netsuite\", \"quickbooks\", \"workday\", \"bamboohr\", \"gusto\",\n    \"intercom\", \"zendesk\", \"linkedin\", \"okta\", \"crowdstrike\", \"snyk\",\n    \"deloitte\", \"kpmg\", \"pwc\", \"pricewaterhousecoopers\", \"ey \", \"ernst\",\n    \"carta\", \"pulley\", \"hubspot\", \"sage\", \"planful\", \"workato\", \"peakon\",\n    \"upwork\", \"toptal\", \"xero\"\n]\n\nprint(\"\\n=== TARGETED VENDOR SEARCH ===\")\nresults = []\nfor row in range(2, ws.max_row + 1):\n    vendor_cell = ws.cell(row, 1).value  # Assume vendor name in col 1\n    if vendor_cell:\n        vendor_lower = str(vendor_cell).lower()\n        for t in target_vendors:\n            if t in vendor_lower:\n                # Get all values for this row\n                row_vals = [ws.cell(row, c).value for c in range(1, min(ws.max_column+1, 15))]\n                results.append((row, row_vals))\n                print(f\"Row {row}: {row_vals}\")\n                break\n\nprint(f\"\\nTotal matches: {len(results)}\")\n```\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017whx8DbFMNrVBET8tyYpbD","session_id":"287e74d1-c222-46fc-97c3-6b14ad8ff5d8","uuid":"f7e9309f-59e2-4a4e-9082-65cb21bc007b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T21:42:28.943Z"}
